The paper discusses feature selection in reinforcement learning, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. The use of Gaussian processes and Bayesian model selection also suggests a focus on probabilistic modeling and inference. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.ML (Machine Learning).
